Not a bigspin or a back tail

Brad @skatemental , Abe and I spreading and shredding with Sir Travis’ ashes in some of the spots that we used to skate together every day in our youth. I first met Travis as a 10 year old on top of the hill where he is playing guitar. We skated down it millions of times together. The last time that Travis was in California in 2017 he called me from the hill and asked me to meet him there. In 1994, Brad showed up at our high school as a transfer student from Ohio. Travis recognized him to be a fellow skateboarder so he invited him over to our lunch spot. One of the first tricks that Travis and I learned together was a feeble grind on this old red curb seen here. I’m happy that I got to grind with part of him again as I held him in a tiny jar. The rest of Travis’ ashes will be spread in more conventionally beautiful places, but I thought it was important to bring him back to some of the dirty old parking lots where we spent so many lovely moments. The old footage of Travis was filmed by @skatemental , @colinrprice and myself. We will love you forever, Travis! Sound on
